ETON	1
MONTEM.	1
[Extracted	1
from	1
the	1
"Courier"	1
of	1
May,	1
1799.]	1
"Yesterday	1
this	1
triennial	1
ceremony	1
took	1
place,	1
with	1
which	1
the	1
public	1
are	1
too	1
well	1
acquainted	1
to	1
require	1
a	1
particular	1
description.	1
A	1
collection,	1
called	1
Salt,	1
is	1
taken	1
from	1
the	1
public,	1
which	1
forms	1
a	1
purse,	1
to	1
support	1
the	1
Captain	1
of	1
the	1
School	1
in	1
his	1
studies	1
at	1
Cambridge.	1
This	1
collection	1
is	1
made	1
by	1
the	1
Scholars,	1
dressed	1
in	1
fancy	1
dresses,	1
all	1
round	1
the	1
country.	1
"At	1
