THE	1
LITTLE	1
MERCHANTS.	1
CHAPTER	1
I.	1
Chi	1
di	1
gallina	1
nasce,	1
convien	1
che	1
rozole.	1
As	1
the	1
old	1
cock	1
crows,	1
so	1
crows	1
the	1
young.	1
Those	1
who	1
have	1
visited	1
Italy	1
give	1
us	1
an	1
agreeable	1
picture	1
of	1
the	1
cheerful	1
industry	1
of	1
the	1
children	1
of	1
all	1
ages	1
in	1
the	1
celebrated	1
city	1
of	1
Naples.	1
Their	1
manner	1
of	1
living	1
and	1
their	1
numerous	1
employments	1
are	1
exactly	1
described	1
in	1
the	1
following	1
"Extract	1
from	1
a	1
Traveller's	1
Journal."	1
*	1
*	1
Varieties	1
of	1
Literature,	1
vol.	1
i.	1
p.	1
299.	1
"The	1
children	1
are	1
busied	1
in	1
various	1
ways.	1
A	1
great	1
number	1
of	1
them	1
bring	1
fish	1
for	1
sale	1
to	1
town	1
from	1
Santa	1
Lucia;	1
others	1
are	1
very	1
often	1
seen	1
about	1
the	1
arsenals,	1
or	1
wherever	1
carpenters	1
are	1
at	1
work,	1
employed	1
in	1
gathering	1
up	1
the	1
chips	1
and	1
pieces	1
of	1
wood;	1
or	1
by	1
the	1
sea-side,	1
picking	1
up	1
sticks,	1
and	1
whatever	1
else	1
has	1
drifted	1
ashore,	1
which,	1
when	1
their	1
basket	1
is	1
full,	1
they	1
carry	1
away.	1
"Children	1
of	1
two	1
or	1
three	1
years	1
old,	1
who	1
can	1
scarcely	1
crawl	1
along	1
upon	1
the	1
ground,	1
in	1
company	1
with	1
boys	1
of	1
five	1
or	1
six,	1
are	1
employed	1
in	1
this	1
pretty	1
trade.	1
Hence	1
they	1
proceed	1
with	1
their	1
baskets	1
into	1
the	1
heart	1
of	1
the	1
city,	1
where	1
in	1
several	1
places	1
they	1
form	1
a	1
sort	1
of	1
little	1
market,	1
sitting	1
round	1
with	1
their	1
stock	1
of	1
wood	1
before	1
them.	1
Labourers,	1
and	1
the	1
lower	1
order	1
of	1
citizens,	1
buy	1
it	1
of	1
them	1
to	1
burn	1
in	1
the	1
tripods	1
for	1
warming	1
themselves,	1
or	1
to	1
use	1
in	1
their	1
scanty	1
kitchens.	1
"Other	1
children	1
carry	1
about	1
for	1
sale	1
the	1
water	1
of	1
the	1
sulphurous	1
wells,	1
which,	1
particularly	1
in	1
the	1
spring	1
season,	1
is	1
drunk	1
in	1
great	1
abundance.	1
Others	1
again	1
endeavour	1
to	1
turn	1
a	1
few	1
pence	1
by	1
buying	1
a	1
small	1
matter	1
of	1
fruit,	1
of	1
pressed	1
honey,	1
cakes,	1
and	1
comfits,	1
and	1
then,	1
like	1
little	1
peddlers,	1
offer	1
and	1
sell	1
them	1
to	1
other	1
children,	1
always	1
for	1
no	1
more	1
profit	1
than	1
that	1
they	1
may	1
have	1
their	1
share	1
of	1
them	1
free	1
of	1
expense.	1
"It	1
is	1
really	1
curious	1
to	1
see	1
how	1
an	1
urchin,	1
whose	1
whole	1
stock	1
and	1
property	1
consist	1
in	1
a	1
board	1
and	1
a	1
knife,	1
will	1
